5 SECTION 5. Article 1 of Chapter 143C of the General Statutes is amended by adding
6 a new section to read:
7 "§ 143C-1-6. Types of State agency transfers.
8 (a) Type I. – A Type I transfer is a transfer of an existing State agency to a principal State
9 department. Under a Type I transfer, all of the following apply:
10 (1) The State agency's statutory authority, powers, duties, and functions,
11 including its management functions, are transferred to a principal State
12 department.
13 (2) The State agency's records, personnel, property, unexpended balances of
14 appropriations, allocations, and other funds are transferred to the principal
15 State department.
16 (3) The State agency's powers, duties, and functions, including rulemaking,
17 regulation, licensing, setting rates and standards, and rendering findings,
18 orders, and adjudications are transferred to the principal State department.
19 (b) Type II. – A Type II transfer is an intact transfer of a State agency to a principal State
20 department. Under a Type II transfer, the transferred State agency shall be administered under
21 the direction and supervision of the principal State department but shall exercise its statutory
22 powers and functions, other than its management functions, independently of the head of the
23 principal State department. The State agency's management functions shall be performed under
24 the direction and supervision of the head of the principal State department.
25 (c) Management Functions. – As used in this section, "management functions" means
26 planning, organizing, staffing, directing, coordinating, reporting, and budgeting."
