42 (1) Agency: whenever the term "agency" is used it shall mean and include, as the
43 context may require, an existing Agency. – A department, institution,
44 commission, committee, board, division, bureau, officer officer, or official.
45 (2) Board: a Board. – A collective body which that assists the head of a principal
46 department or his or her designee in the development of major programs
47 programs, including the tender of advice on departmental priorities.
48 (3) Commission: a Commission. – A collective body which that adopts rules and
49 regulations in a quasi-legislative manner and which acts in a quasi-judicial
50 capacity in rendering findings or decisions involving differing interests.
