1 of the business of the production or sale of tobacco. The term does not include
2 the manufacturing of tobacco products or the sale of tobacco products at
3 wholesale or retail.
4 (9) Tobacco-related employment. – Employment in a tobacco-related business, or
5 in the manufacturing of tobacco products or the component products used in
6 the manufacture of tobacco products. The term does not include persons
7 employed in the sale of tobacco products at wholesale or retail.
8 "§ 143-717. Commission.
9 (a) Creation. – The Tobacco Trust Fund Commission is created. The Commission shall
10 be administratively located within the Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services but
11 shall exercise its powers independently of the Commissioner of Agriculture and the Department.
12 All administrative expenses of the Commission shall be paid from the Fund.
13 (b) Membership. – The Commission shall consist of 18 members. The Commission shall
14 be appointed as follows: six members by the Governor, six members by the President Pro
15 Tempore of the Senate, and six members by the Speaker of the House of Representatives. The
16 members shall be appointed as follows:
